properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 9 at 6:34PM EST until January 10 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Caribou ME
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
seas 6 to 9 feet expected on the coastal waters and 2 to 4 feet
on the intra coastal waters.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Eastport, ME to Schoodic Point, ME
out 25 NM, Coastal Waters from Schoodic Point, ME to
Stonington, ME out 25 NM and Intra Coastal Waters from
Schoodic Point, ME to Stonington, ME.

* WHEN...From 7 AM to 4 PM EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM TO 4 PM EST FRIDAY
